        <h1>Deviation from mean elevation</h1>

        <p>This tool can be used to calculate the difference between the elevation of 
            each grid cell and the mean elevation of the centering local neighbourhood,
            normalized by standard deviation. Therefore, this index of topographic 
            residual is essentially equivalent to a local <i>z<i>-score. This attribute 
            measures the relative topographic position as a fraction of local relief, 
            and so is normalized to the local surface roughness.</p>
                
            <p>The user must specify the name of the input digital elevation model (DEM), 
            the name of the output file, and the size of the neighbourhood. Neighbourhood 
            size is specified in map units, e.g. metres.</p>

